1
00:00:25,412 --> 00:00:26,467
My name is Odd Thomas.

2
00:00:26,502 --> 00:00:30,256
Though in this age when fame is the
altar at which most people worship.

3
00:00:30,291 --> 00:00:31,765
I'm not sure why you should care.

4
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:34,219
I'm not a celebrity.
I'm not the child of a celebrity.

5
00:00:34,254 --> 00:00:36,009
I've never been married to,
abused by,

6
00:00:36,044 --> 00:00:37,764
or provided a kidney to a celebrity.

7
00:00:37,799 --> 00:00:39,093
Green Moon Bowling.

8
00:00:41,810 --> 00:00:45,262
But I do lead an unusual life.

9
00:00:52,780 --> 00:00:54,856
Penny Kalisto.

10
00:01:05,606 --> 00:01:08,074
My name really is Odd.

11
00:01:08,109 --> 00:01:11,485
According to my mother, it was
a screw-up on my birth certificate.

12
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:14,861
She says I was supposed to be called
Todd, after a Lithuanian uncle.

13
00:01:15,283 --> 00:01:17,542
My father insists my name
was always Odd...

14
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:20,827
and he notes that all of
my uncles are Bulgarian.

15
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:24,101
My father claims
my mother is insane.

16
00:01:24,136 --> 00:01:26,872
My mother, of course,
begs to differ.

17
00:01:27,588 --> 00:01:32,795
My abilities are a gift from God!

18
00:01:33,552 --> 00:01:35,510
My father won that argument.

19
00:01:36,764 --> 00:01:40,429
I was 12 years old when they finally
locked her up and threw away the key.

20
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:49,604
I've come to believe that
my mother and I share certain...

21
00:01:49,694 --> 00:01:51,119
abilities.

22
00:01:51,154 --> 00:01:53,865
Since I don't want to be locked up
with the key thrown away...

23
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:58,029
I've pretty much kept mine a secret.

24
00:02:05,961 --> 00:02:07,421
Odd Thomas.

25
00:02:07,456 --> 00:02:08,846
Hello, Harlo.

26
00:02:08,881 --> 00:02:10,431
Long time, no see.

27
00:02:10,466 --> 00:02:13,386
Whoa! Whoa! Hey, hey.
Come on, man. No touchy, no feely.

28
00:02:13,421 --> 00:02:16,463
- Sorry, but I love this car.
- I know.

29
00:02:16,498 --> 00:02:19,505
It's too bad a car
can't love you back.

30
00:02:22,145 --> 00:02:24,374
What's wrong, Odd?
There anything I can do?

31
00:02:24,409 --> 00:02:26,603
No, it's something
you've already done.

32
00:02:27,442 --> 00:02:29,584
Hey! Hey! Come on-oh, Odd.
No fooling around, man.

33
00:02:29,619 --> 00:02:31,727
- Give me my keys.
- Her blood is in your pocket.

34
00:02:33,699 --> 00:02:35,948
Most people would think
that's a weird thing to say...

35
00:02:35,983 --> 00:02:38,197
but you don't think
it's very weird, do you, Harlo?

36
00:02:45,086 --> 00:02:46,331
On that night...

37
00:02:47,797 --> 00:02:50,300
you took a piece of white felt...

38
00:02:50,335 --> 00:02:52,225
and after killing Penny...

39
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:54,971
you collected some of her blood.

40
00:02:55,006 --> 00:02:57,022
And now it's dry...

41
00:02:57,057 --> 00:03:00,806
and stiff and
brittle like a cracker...

42
00:03:01,645 --> 00:03:05,394
and it's still in your pocket.

43
00:03:13,115 --> 00:03:15,826
In moments like these,
pity tears at me.

44
00:03:15,861 --> 00:03:18,503
And a kind of madness
comes over me...

45
00:03:18,538 --> 00:03:21,249
forcing me to hunt people
like Harlo Landerson...

46
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:25,199
who I have no pity for whatsoever.

47
00:03:42,521 --> 00:03:44,598
Sorry, Mrs. Curtees!

48
00:03:46,484 --> 00:03:48,062
Sorry, Saleen!

49
00:04:21,437 --> 00:04:23,189
What the hell are you doing?

50
00:04:23,224 --> 00:04:25,396
Mom, what's going on?

51
00:04:29,654 --> 00:04:31,528
Stevie, run honey, run!

52
00:04:40,082 --> 00:04:41,113
Come here!

53
00:04:50,009 --> 00:04:52,714
My life is filled with guys
like Harlo Landerson.

54
00:04:56,057 --> 00:04:58,346
And since I like my face
just the way it is...

55
00:04:59,603 --> 00:05:01,263
I learned how to handle myself.

56
00:05:18,039 --> 00:05:22,535
I may see dead people, but then,
by God, I do something about it.

57
00:05:23,378 --> 00:05:25,220
Hey. Hey!

58
00:05:25,255 --> 00:05:27,180
Shift down, man! Go easy.

59
00:05:27,215 --> 00:05:30,133
I'm sorry, sir,
but I don't have a "go easy" gear.

60
00:05:31,303 --> 00:05:33,055
You should probably get that looked at.

61
00:05:33,090 --> 00:05:34,605
Now, Officer Eckles...

62
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,731
does being a police officer

63
00:05:35,766 --> 00:05:37,434
give you the right to beat
the shit out of people?

64
00:05:37,469 --> 00:05:39,068
Not at all, Officer Varner.

65
00:05:39,103 --> 00:05:41,095
But it is one of
the perks of the job.

66
00:05:47,153 --> 00:05:51,316
I believe in a higher power
and the afterlife.

67
00:05:52,992 --> 00:05:54,866
Call me strange.

68
00:05:55,912 --> 00:05:57,128
Others do.

69
00:05:57,163 --> 00:05:59,037
He's so strange.

70
00:06:01,418 --> 00:06:02,759
Don't worry, Penny.

71
00:06:02,794 --> 00:06:06,214
I think where you're going
is a home for the spirit...

72
00:06:06,249 --> 00:06:09,880
and it's filled with
kindness and wonder.

73
00:06:11,011 --> 00:06:12,885
I'm sorry, Penny.

74
00:06:13,430 --> 00:06:16,004
I'm sorry your life was so short.

75
00:06:26,569 --> 00:06:28,229
The dead don't talk.

76
00:06:29,072 --> 00:06:31,148
I don't know why.

77
00:06:35,746 --> 00:06:37,045
Here we are again.

78
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:40,331
Busted furniture and
shattered glass everywhere.

79
00:06:42,294 --> 00:06:44,345
Most of it was not my fault.

80
00:06:44,380 --> 00:06:47,779
Except the panda bear lamp
and the Biffy the Clown mirror.

81
00:06:47,814 --> 00:06:51,143
- That was this guy.
- Why didn't you come to me first..

82
00:06:51,178 --> 00:06:55,016
give me a chance to find a way
to get Harlo to entrap himself?

83
00:06:55,051 --> 00:06:56,149
Whenever we do it that way,

84
00:06:56,184 --> 00:06:58,311
it's always more efficient
and less destructive.

85
00:06:58,346 --> 00:07:00,438
Yes, I know but he had
to be stopped right now...

86
00:07:00,473 --> 00:07:02,645
or he was gonna do it again soon.

87
00:07:03,149 --> 00:07:05,861
That's what Penny wanted to tell me.
That's why she hadn't left yet.

88
00:07:05,896 --> 00:07:09,312
Son, you so complicate my life.

89
00:07:12,117 --> 00:07:13,362
Look.

90
00:07:15,162 --> 00:07:16,253
Besides her blood...

91
00:07:16,288 --> 00:07:20,251
Harlo had these photos of Penny
post-mortem in his wallet.

92
00:07:20,286 --> 00:07:23,042
If there's any fuss about
how you pegged Harlo...

93
00:07:23,077 --> 00:07:25,798
just say he opened up
his wallet to pay off a bet.

94
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:28,593
Five bucks on
yesterday's Dodger's game...

95
00:07:28,628 --> 00:07:30,753
the photos fell out,
you saw em-

96
00:07:30,788 --> 00:07:32,878
He ran and naturally,
I gave chase.

97
00:07:33,515 --> 00:07:34,760
Naturally.

98
00:08:24,819 --> 00:08:28,510
Save me!

99
00:08:28,545 --> 00:08:32,167
Save us!

100
00:08:32,202 --> 00:08:34,141
- Save.
- Us!

101
00:08:34,176 --> 00:08:36,065
- Save..
- Us!

102
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,955
Save you from who?

103
00:08:40,544 --> 00:08:41,789
Who is that?

104
00:08:42,838 --> 00:08:44,213
Who is it?

105
00:09:22,046 --> 00:09:23,623
Evil is coming.

106
00:09:24,131 --> 00:09:27,382
And it's up to me to figure out
who's gonna be holding the gun.

107
00:09:28,427 --> 00:09:29,886
Morning, Elvis.

108
00:09:30,722 --> 00:09:31,604
Pico Mundo Grill.

109
00:09:31,639 --> 00:09:33,273
So much of my life
is out of my control.

110
00:09:33,308 --> 00:09:36,853
I would have gone 7 kinds of
crazy if I hadn't simplified.

111
00:09:36,888 --> 00:09:40,524
So I have no motorized vehicles,
no homeownership...

112
00:09:40,559 --> 00:09:43,527
no insurance,
and no grand ambitions.

113
00:09:43,562 --> 00:09:44,689
Ladies.

114
00:09:45,112 --> 00:09:46,620
Eggs! Wreck em and stretch em!

115
00:09:46,655 --> 00:09:49,283
"Wreck em" means scrambled,
and "stretch em" means...

116
00:09:49,318 --> 00:09:50,499
add an extra egg.

117
00:09:50,534 --> 00:09:51,959
Cardiac shingles and hash browns!

118
00:09:51,994 --> 00:09:55,122
"Cardiac shingles"
are toast with lots of butter.

119
00:09:55,157 --> 00:09:56,850
And hash browns...

120
00:09:56,885 --> 00:09:58,508
are just hash browns.

121
00:09:58,543 --> 00:10:01,247
Not every word
we use is diner lingo.

122
00:10:02,630 --> 00:10:04,138
Just as not every short-order cook

123
00:10:04,173 --> 00:10:08,345
is an undercover detective
for dead people.

124
00:10:08,380 --> 00:10:09,803
Duck.

125
00:10:15,852 --> 00:10:19,154
That is Stormy Lewellyn.

126
00:10:19,189 --> 00:10:23,686
Stormy and I are destined
to be together forever.

127
00:10:27,948 --> 00:10:32,112
You are destined
to be together forever.

128
00:10:35,039 --> 00:10:37,661
Hey, Chief.
Tummy Tickler coming at ya.

129
00:10:41,713 --> 00:10:44,132
You know, I'm still not happy
about what you did yesterday, Oddie.

130
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:45,384
You could have
gotten yourself killed.

131
00:10:45,419 --> 00:10:48,060
I am not afraid of death.

132
00:10:48,095 --> 00:10:50,586
Of course, I'm not ready to go
on a date with him, either.

133
00:10:57,062 --> 00:10:58,731
Would you throw yourself
off a cliff for me?

134
00:10:58,766 --> 00:10:59,614
Of course I would.

135
00:10:59,649 --> 00:11:02,485
Into a river of razor blades
and lemon juice?

136
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,701
Absolutely.

137
00:11:03,736 --> 00:11:06,114
Of course, I'd like to know
the reasoning behind such a request..

138
00:11:06,149 --> 00:11:08,164
but, fortunately for me...

139
00:11:08,199 --> 00:11:11,536
you reek of intelligence
and integrity.

140
00:11:11,571 --> 00:11:13,830
And you reek of peach shampoo.

141
00:11:13,865 --> 00:11:16,238
Just the way I like you.

142
00:11:17,501 --> 00:11:19,635
- Chief.
- Morning, Stormy.

143
00:11:19,670 --> 00:11:21,964
What's with
the cat-ate-the-canary smile?

144
00:11:21,999 --> 00:11:23,838
Tonight is date night.

145
00:11:24,591 --> 00:11:26,880
So you think you're
gonna get yourself some, huh?

146
00:11:27,178 --> 00:11:30,222
- I wouldn't put it quite that way.
- Stormy Special.

147
00:11:30,257 --> 00:11:32,299
- Girlfriend.
- Morning, dude.

148
00:11:50,243 --> 00:11:51,877
I call them bodachs.

149
00:11:51,912 --> 00:11:53,545
Well, not to their faces, I hope.

150
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:55,953
I never met anybody
that could see em before.

151
00:11:56,166 --> 00:11:58,878
- Neither have I.
- Everyone told me it's in my head.

152
00:11:58,913 --> 00:12:00,463
Well, you should stop
telling everyone.

153
00:12:00,498 --> 00:12:02,096
I tried telling my parents.

154
00:12:02,131 --> 00:12:03,674
If I told my parents,
I'd ve spent my whole life...

155
00:12:03,709 --> 00:12:05,567
picking winning lottery numbers.

156
00:12:05,602 --> 00:12:07,425
You can pick winning lotto numbers?

157
00:12:07,845 --> 00:12:10,682
- No, I can't. Stay on point.
- Right. Yeah.

158
00:12:10,717 --> 00:12:13,810
Yesterday, when I finally saw one...

159
00:12:13,845 --> 00:12:15,979
I gave him the finger, Homes.

160
00:12:16,014 --> 00:12:17,404
Don't you know?

161
00:12:17,439 --> 00:12:20,974
If they find out you can see them,
they will kill you.

162
00:12:27,658 --> 00:12:29,236
They will kill you.

163
00:13:05,406 --> 00:13:07,039
- Little advice?
- Yeah?

164
00:13:07,074 --> 00:13:09,042
Karla prefers chocolate to flowers

165
00:13:09,077 --> 00:13:11,579
and you should get
yourself some candles.

166
00:13:11,614 --> 00:13:12,610
Candles?

167
00:13:13,122 --> 00:13:14,700
Thanks. Good idea.

168
00:13:20,338 --> 00:13:21,972
Whew, close.

169
00:13:22,007 --> 00:13:23,675
That would have been
a little awkward.

170
00:13:23,710 --> 00:13:26,132
You two are really something.

171
00:13:26,167 --> 00:13:28,520
I don't know what, but something.

172
00:13:28,555 --> 00:13:31,058
We're weird and screwed up
but we're okay.

173
00:13:31,093 --> 00:13:32,303
I don't know.

174
00:13:32,518 --> 00:13:33,977
You are...

175
00:13:35,146 --> 00:13:36,445
so cool.

176
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:40,151
So, you deny me my weirdness,
but agree that I'm screwed up?

177
00:13:40,186 --> 00:13:41,784
You're right.
I see your problem.

178
00:13:41,819 --> 00:13:44,113
Weirdness, it can be fun.
It can be kind of cool.

179
00:13:44,148 --> 00:13:47,867
Screwed-up-ness, not so much.

180
00:13:47,902 --> 00:13:50,655
You are quite weird.

181
00:13:52,247 --> 00:13:55,459
- Apology accepted.
- I gotta go. Be good, you two.

182
00:13:55,494 --> 00:13:58,086
It's not me you have to worry about.

183
00:13:58,121 --> 00:13:59,415
Don't I know it.

184
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:02,258
I gotta go to work, too, Oddie.

185
00:14:02,293 --> 00:14:04,546
- Okay.
- Later, my love.

186
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:16,434
Stormy!

187
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:26,942
Miss you already.

188
00:14:31,872 --> 00:14:33,624
- Living up to his name.
- Every damn day.

189
00:14:33,659 --> 00:14:34,869
Later.

190
00:14:35,292 --> 00:14:39,046
Months often pass
when I don't see a single bodach.

191
00:14:39,081 --> 00:14:39,971
When they do show up...

192
00:14:40,006 --> 00:14:43,134
it's a sure sign that carnage
and bloodshed are not far behind.

193
00:14:43,169 --> 00:14:44,017
Morning.

194
00:14:44,052 --> 00:14:46,258
They don't cause it.
They feed on it.

195
00:14:46,888 --> 00:14:50,506
The more bodachs that show up,
the bigger the eventual feast.

196
00:14:52,936 --> 00:14:55,438
They're attracted to evil
like bees to flowers.

197
00:14:55,473 --> 00:14:57,941
They know when death is coming
and want to watch.

198
00:14:57,976 --> 00:15:00,284
They don't show up
for any ordinary death.

199
00:15:00,319 --> 00:15:04,613
They want extreme,
operatic violence and terror.

200
00:15:06,784 --> 00:15:09,704
Penny Kalisto's death
wasn't horrific enough...

201
00:15:09,739 --> 00:15:13,452
to bring a single bodach
into our world.

202
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:20,123
This town is in serious trouble.

203
00:15:21,299 --> 00:15:23,385
- Bye, Oddie.
- See you, ladies.

204
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:25,259
Nicolina! Levanna!

205
00:15:29,099 --> 00:15:31,804
Odd, am I really sucking
at this whole "mother" thing?

206
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:35,321
Well, considering their
last one was a junkie...

207
00:15:35,356 --> 00:15:37,983
who left them in your lap
when you were barely 18...

208
00:15:38,018 --> 00:15:41,612
I think you rather rock, Vi.

209
00:15:41,647 --> 00:15:42,643
See you later.

210
00:15:43,197 --> 00:15:45,123
I'm heading this way, too.

211
00:15:45,158 --> 00:15:47,514
Gonna go see Madame Pearl,
get myself read.

212
00:15:47,549 --> 00:15:49,836
Personally,
I don't believe people who say...

213
00:15:49,871 --> 00:15:52,999
they can read minds or palms
and, trust me, tea leaves...

214
00:15:53,034 --> 00:15:54,716
just cloggage
in the garbage disposal.

215
00:15:54,751 --> 00:15:57,796
It's just I had this dream
last night you would not believe.

216
00:15:57,831 --> 00:16:01,550
Well, anything short of
a 9-alarm massacre, I can top.

217
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:04,255
I'd never seen myself face-on
in a dream before.

218
00:16:05,596 --> 00:16:07,021
You saw your own face?

219
00:16:07,056 --> 00:16:10,601
Me and this guy, we were
both lying dead all busted up...

220
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:13,306
like we'd been shot
to pieces or something.

221
00:16:18,526 --> 00:16:20,702
You know, I wouldn't worry
about it, Vi.

222
00:16:20,737 --> 00:16:22,813
I mean, have any of
your dreams ever come true?

223
00:16:23,740 --> 00:16:24,903
No.

224
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:28,245
I know most people think
you're just quirky or weird, Odd...

225
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:30,330
except Stormy who thinks
angels fly out of your butt.

226
00:16:30,365 --> 00:16:32,082
But I know there's more to it.

227
00:16:32,117 --> 00:16:33,632
You have a secret.

228
00:16:33,667 --> 00:16:35,592
You're either a clairvoyant...

229
00:16:35,627 --> 00:16:37,887
a psychic, a seer,
a soothsayer, or something.

230
00:16:37,922 --> 00:16:40,132
Or you got yourself some juice
with a higher power.

231
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:41,015
And I need to know.

232
00:16:41,050 --> 00:16:42,924
Tell me the truth now, Odd.

233
00:16:43,761 --> 00:16:45,837
Do you see death in me?

234
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:53,563
No. No, all I see
is my own insensitivity...

235
00:16:53,598 --> 00:16:57,015
and a long,
happy life for you, okay?

236
00:17:00,862 --> 00:17:04,611
Hey, Vi, the the dead guy
in your dream, what was he wearing?

237
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:07,327
Wearing? I don't know.

238
00:17:07,362 --> 00:17:09,587
Oh! Wait. Yeah...

239
00:17:09,622 --> 00:17:14,118
a red and black shirt with
black bowling balls on it.

240
00:17:20,883 --> 00:17:23,928
One of my stranger abilities is
that when I need to find someone...

241
00:17:23,963 --> 00:17:26,479
like right now, the creepy
guy in the diner,

242
00:17:26,514 --> 00:17:30,477
I can randomly wander around, and
pretty quickly, I'll run into him.

243
00:17:30,512 --> 00:17:32,885
This is a talent for
which I have no name.

244
00:17:33,188 --> 00:17:36,108
Stormy calls it psychic magnetism.

245
00:17:36,143 --> 00:17:38,701
Super Summer Sale.

246
00:17:38,736 --> 00:17:41,620
That's Tom Jedd.
He was my little league coach.

247
00:17:41,655 --> 00:17:45,826
Been hanging around Tire World for
years, although I don't know why.

248
00:17:45,861 --> 00:17:48,204
His death was not caused
by a defective tire.

249
00:17:48,239 --> 00:17:51,953
Such a beautiful girl-

250
00:17:57,797 --> 00:18:01,468
There is something about
