00:50:38,105 --> 00:50:40,816
Hey, Chief. What's with
the guy who shot the dogs?

744
00:50:40,851 --> 00:50:42,450
His name's Kevin Goss.

745
00:50:42,485 --> 00:50:44,535
He was teaching a class
from 6:00 to 10:00...

746
00:50:44,570 --> 00:50:47,365
then he went to Starbucks
till they closed at midnight.

747
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:49,773
He got home about
two minutes too late.

748
00:50:50,076 --> 00:50:53,955
Sir? I've actually seen
those Rottweilers before.

749
00:50:53,990 --> 00:50:55,829
They belong to Bob Robertson.

750
00:50:58,961 --> 00:51:00,419
All right!

751
00:51:00,838 --> 00:51:04,174
I want an A. P. B.
put out on this guy now!

752
00:51:04,209 --> 00:51:05,474
- Find him!
- Yes, sir.

753
00:51:05,509 --> 00:51:08,554
Simon, I want you to go back
over to Robertson's house.

754
00:51:08,589 --> 00:51:10,222
I'll have a search
warrant in the morning

755
00:51:10,257 --> 00:51:11,439
as soon as the courthouse opens.

756
00:51:11,474 --> 00:51:15,228
Sir, no offense, but I wasted most
of the day staking out that house.

757
00:51:15,263 --> 00:51:18,982
Then I went to the bowling alley
and stayed there until they closed.

758
00:51:19,017 --> 00:51:20,310
Nothing happened.

759
00:51:20,942 --> 00:51:23,564
Nobody showed.
It was a complete waste of my time.

760
00:51:24,195 --> 00:51:29,190
Sir, are we sure this Robertson
character isn't just a wild goose chase?

761
00:51:29,701 --> 00:51:31,703
Exactly where were you between
the hours of 8:00 and 10:00?

762
00:51:31,738 --> 00:51:35,452
- He was with me the whole time.
- Just ease up.

763
00:51:35,749 --> 00:51:38,794
Now go check the house again
and ask around about the dogs.

764
00:51:38,829 --> 00:51:40,123
Yes, sir.

765
00:51:42,340 --> 00:51:43,454
You two.

766
00:51:44,008 --> 00:51:45,123
Home.

767
00:51:45,760 --> 00:51:46,923
Go, now!

768
00:51:51,808 --> 00:51:55,972
I think you should wear this.
Try not to laugh.

769
00:52:04,238 --> 00:52:06,949
Oddie, you are not responsible
for every death you can't prevent.

770
00:52:06,984 --> 00:52:07,831
She died.

771
00:52:07,866 --> 00:52:10,911
And if Fungus Bob was her killer,
I was either slow or stupid.

772
00:52:10,946 --> 00:52:12,003
Choose your weapon.

773
00:52:12,038 --> 00:52:13,796
Why would Fungus Bob kill Lysette?

774
00:52:13,831 --> 00:52:15,548
What's the connection?
It makes no sense.

775
00:52:15,583 --> 00:52:19,879
It doesn't have to make sense.
It just has to satisfy some sick urge.

776
00:52:19,914 --> 00:52:21,753
Maybe he's warming up.

777
00:52:22,465 --> 00:52:25,302
I think the chief just sent
some detectives to protect you.

778
00:52:25,337 --> 00:52:27,045
I don't need protecting.

779
00:52:28,221 --> 00:52:31,341
Actually I think it might
just be surveillance.

780
00:52:32,267 --> 00:52:33,609
Fungus Bob followed me
to the church.

781
00:52:33,644 --> 00:52:36,230
I bet the chief is hoping
he'll sniff me out again.

782
00:52:36,265 --> 00:52:37,863
If the chief is using you as bait...

783
00:52:37,898 --> 00:52:41,018
he should at least ask if
you mind having a hook in your ass.

784
00:52:46,365 --> 00:52:50,198
Oh, man, I got to stay focused.

785
00:52:52,288 --> 00:52:55,206
Good. You keep an eye on my girl.

786
00:52:56,376 --> 00:52:58,250
August 15th had begun.

787
00:52:58,670 --> 00:53:00,413
Time was running out.

788
00:53:47,471 --> 00:53:48,930
Hey, Bob.

789
00:53:50,057 --> 00:53:51,931
You're not planning
on getting up, are ya?

790
00:53:55,814 --> 00:53:57,474
But if you're dead...

791
00:53:57,899 --> 00:54:00,390
who's gonna massacre Pico Mundo?

792
00:54:01,111 --> 00:54:04,147
Gun on the floor,
dead guy in my tub.

793
00:54:04,656 --> 00:54:06,945
I know a setup when I see one.

794
00:54:07,993 --> 00:54:11,329
But if I call the police,
the chief will have to arrest me...

795
00:54:11,364 --> 00:54:14,665
and I won't be able to stop
the catastrophe from happening.

796
00:54:24,886 --> 00:54:26,519
Oh, my God!

797
00:54:26,554 --> 00:54:28,761
Oh, you are creeping me out.

798
00:54:43,238 --> 00:54:45,112
You're freezing cold, Bob.

799
00:54:45,950 --> 00:54:48,867
Your rigor mortis is way advanced.

800
00:54:50,121 --> 00:54:52,113
You know...

801
00:54:52,331 --> 00:54:54,834
the chief said
you didn't leave any fingerprints.

802
00:54:54,869 --> 00:54:56,708
He didn't leave a single print.

803
00:54:58,588 --> 00:55:01,791
And Stormy never actually saw you.

804
00:55:02,634 --> 00:55:04,009
- Come on!
- What?

805
00:55:07,973 --> 00:55:09,996
Because you were already dead.

806
00:55:10,031 --> 00:55:11,984
And the whole time in the church,

807
00:55:12,019 --> 00:55:14,688
you were actually
a pissed-off poltergeist.

808
00:55:14,723 --> 00:55:17,323
I think the last time
I saw Fungus Bob alive...

809
00:55:17,358 --> 00:55:20,478
was when he left his house
right before I broke into it.

810
00:55:21,737 --> 00:55:25,741
He's been haunting me ever since,
blaming me for his death.

811
00:55:25,776 --> 00:55:29,746
Why he blames me or who the hell
killed him is a little hazy.

812
00:55:29,781 --> 00:55:32,471
If I'm caught,
I'll either be arrested for murder

813
00:55:32,506 --> 00:55:35,161
or rolling what looks like
the biggest joint ever.

814
00:55:52,270 --> 00:55:54,262
It's just me, Rosalia!

815
00:56:07,494 --> 00:56:09,487
Damn it.

816
00:56:10,956 --> 00:56:13,328
Oh, give me a break.

817
00:56:15,002 --> 00:56:17,493
It's just me, again, Rosalia.

818
00:56:18,964 --> 00:56:21,675
I'm gonna borrow
your car again, okay?

819
00:56:21,710 --> 00:56:23,017
If I'm being framed,

820
00:56:23,052 --> 00:56:25,905
why the police have failed
to arrive and arrest me...

821
00:56:25,940 --> 00:56:28,758
or the murderer hasn't come
to kill me, I do not know.

822
00:56:41,071 --> 00:56:44,573
All right, Bob, where can I put you
to quietly decompose for a while...

823
00:56:44,608 --> 00:56:48,075
before someone finds you and has
a new love of Jesus scared into em?

824
00:57:06,848 --> 00:57:08,481
Interesting story, Bob.

825
00:57:08,516 --> 00:57:11,436
After the federal government
abandoned this prison...

826
00:57:11,471 --> 00:57:13,779
it went through a long
series of owners.

827
00:57:13,814 --> 00:57:18,402
Rumor has it that at Von Zipper's
Burgers the fries were delicious...

828
00:57:18,437 --> 00:57:21,853
and the free-soft-drink-refill
policy was generously honored.

829
00:57:24,867 --> 00:57:27,335
And yet, this fine
dining establishment...

830
00:57:27,370 --> 00:57:32,166
never succeeded in winning
over the family-dining crowd...

831
00:57:32,201 --> 00:57:35,701
which is so essential
to any restaurant operation.

832
00:57:36,671 --> 00:57:38,805
Welcome to the gas chamber.

833
00:57:38,840 --> 00:57:40,508
A lot of people died in here, Bob.

834
00:57:40,543 --> 00:57:42,176
You should feel right at home.

835
00:57:57,401 --> 00:58:01,155
Stormy's always joking about running
off to Las Vegas and getting married.

836
00:58:01,190 --> 00:58:04,200
But I tell her Vegas is packed
with dead people and bad guys...

837
00:58:04,235 --> 00:58:07,201
and I'd just end up
fighting evil 24-7.

838
00:58:09,414 --> 00:58:11,490
I should have listened to her.

839
00:58:14,211 --> 00:58:15,325
Too many.

840
00:58:16,797 --> 00:58:18,457
Too many.

841
00:58:39,529 --> 00:58:41,288
The chief.

842
00:58:41,323 --> 00:58:42,651
I need the chief.

843
00:58:44,743 --> 00:58:46,501
Dear Lord.

844
00:58:46,536 --> 00:58:50,071
If that's you again, Odd,
we are going to have words!

845
00:59:01,761 --> 00:59:03,837
Oh, my God.

846
00:59:11,563 --> 00:59:13,748
No offense, Odd Thomas,
but I can't think of anybody...

847
00:59:13,783 --> 00:59:15,933
who could come in here right now
and not get my back up.

848
00:59:16,234 --> 00:59:18,591
- So you think he knew the shooter?
- Had to.

849
00:59:18,626 --> 00:59:20,948
Which means it's probably
somebody I know, too.

850
00:59:20,983 --> 00:59:23,439
- How bad is he?
- Bad.

851
00:59:24,994 --> 00:59:27,282
- Well, he's a fighter.
- He better be.

852
00:59:28,748 --> 00:59:30,727
- Hey, Bern.
- Ma'am.

853
00:59:34,921 --> 00:59:37,494
- Hey.
- Oh Oddie.

854
00:59:37,715 --> 00:59:40,760
Keep those reporters out of here.
You, on that door.

855
00:59:40,795 --> 00:59:43,049
- Sorry, no press inside.
- Comin through.

856
00:59:46,183 --> 00:59:48,140
You saved his life, Oddie.

857
00:59:49,186 --> 00:59:50,977
Where's this bullet?

858
00:59:51,480 --> 00:59:54,185
That's the one they're
trying to dig out of him now.

859
00:59:57,945 --> 00:59:59,938
Time is up.

860
01:00:00,156 --> 01:00:04,948
Pico Mundo is awakening
to a horror that only I can stop.

861
01:00:05,870 --> 01:00:08,122
Lysette and Fungus Bob are dead.

862
01:00:08,157 --> 01:00:10,340
The chief is
in the emergency room.

863
01:00:10,375 --> 01:00:13,294
There's hoards of bodachs
swarming all over town.

864
01:00:13,329 --> 01:00:15,011
Whatever's coming is gonna be big.

865
01:00:15,046 --> 01:00:17,722
I'm scared,
and I'm supposed to be fearless.

866
01:00:17,757 --> 01:00:19,947
- Don't tell me to stay home today.
- Please stay home today.

867
01:00:19,982 --> 01:00:22,137
- I will if you stay home with me.
- We've been through this.

868
01:00:22,172 --> 01:00:24,640
I have to do
whatever I can to stop it.

869
01:00:24,675 --> 01:00:26,607
Is Viola going to be shot dead?

870
01:00:26,642 --> 01:00:28,931
You know I don't know
that for sure.

871
01:00:29,353 --> 01:00:31,927
She's had it hard in life.
She doesn't need this.

872
01:00:32,565 --> 01:00:34,949
Shot dead? Really?
Who does need it?

873
01:00:34,984 --> 01:00:37,570
Oh, I don't know
why I try to reason with you.

874
01:00:37,605 --> 01:00:38,703
I always lose.

875
01:00:38,738 --> 01:00:40,761
You're a fabulous man of action,
odd one.

876
01:00:40,796 --> 01:00:42,784
You don't need to be
a good debater, too.

877
01:00:42,819 --> 01:00:44,542
Besides, you said yourself...

878
01:00:44,577 --> 01:00:47,289
any road I choose could lead me
right back to the same fate.

879
01:00:47,324 --> 01:00:49,458
So, which is it?
Do I have free will?

880
01:00:49,493 --> 01:00:51,118
Am I in God's hands?

881
01:00:51,960 --> 01:00:52,968
Or is it both?

882
01:00:53,003 --> 01:00:55,297
Have I ever told you
you've got a lot of issues?

883
01:00:55,332 --> 01:00:57,056
I'm a woman. We all have issues.

884
01:00:57,091 --> 01:01:00,156
It's what keeps us interesting,
and you men interested.

885
01:01:00,191 --> 01:01:03,222
Oh, yeah? It's what makes us
crazy and die younger.

886
01:01:03,257 --> 01:01:04,467
Do you love me?

887
01:01:05,224 --> 01:01:07,393
I love you more than life itself.

888
01:01:07,428 --> 01:01:10,228
See? It's working.

889
01:01:15,944 --> 01:01:18,780
Don't look back. Don't look back.

890
01:01:18,815 --> 01:01:20,025
Give him strength.

891
01:01:23,994 --> 01:01:25,453
Knock, knock.

892
01:01:30,459 --> 01:01:33,246
I'm hoping Bob left
a clue on his computer.

893
01:01:34,088 --> 01:01:36,496
Something to lead me
to his partner...

894
01:01:38,259 --> 01:01:40,970
to the person who was
planning on killing 100s,

895
01:01:41,005 --> 01:01:44,007
if not 1000s of people.

896
01:02:44,495 --> 01:02:45,503
Hey.

897
01:02:45,538 --> 01:02:47,290
Loop me in, odd one.
Where are you?

898
01:02:47,325 --> 01:02:49,180
I'm walking towards the fridge.

899
01:02:49,215 --> 01:02:51,035
Yours, mine, or Fungus Bob's?

900
01:02:52,629 --> 01:02:54,137
Don't "uh-huh" me. I told you...

901
01:02:54,172 --> 01:02:56,883
you are not allowed to go playing
around in any more hell gates.

902
01:02:56,918 --> 01:02:58,461
Next!

903
01:02:58,760 --> 01:03:01,112
Oh, God. Cockroaches.

904
01:03:01,147 --> 01:03:03,464
Always cockroaches.

905
01:03:03,682 --> 01:03:06,060
- Odd Thomas, did you hear me?
- Which part?

906
01:03:06,095 --> 01:03:07,276
I can't believe
you went back there.

907
01:03:07,311 --> 01:03:10,645
Every time you don't listen to me,
you get yourself into trouble.

908
01:03:11,190 --> 01:03:14,524
- I wish I'd listened to you.
- You get out of there right now.

909
01:03:14,819 --> 01:03:17,737
Right, right. Leaving. Leaving.

910
01:03:20,784 --> 01:03:23,495
Never heard you make that
sound before. Is everything okay?

911
01:03:23,530 --> 01:03:27,327
- Yeah.
- What are you looking at?

912
01:03:28,917 --> 01:03:29,925
Fingers.

913
01:03:29,960 --> 01:03:32,546
Please say they're attached
to someone's hand.

914
01:03:32,581 --> 01:03:33,762
Sorry.

915
01:03:33,797 --> 01:03:35,014
Get out of there, Oddie.

916
01:03:35,049 --> 01:03:38,267
Someone has been buying
a lot of Burke and Bailey's.

917
01:03:38,302 --> 01:03:40,471
Yeah? Well, you tell whoever's
buying it that our ice cream...

918
01:03:40,506 --> 01:03:43,092
may be the best,
but it'll still melt in hell.

919
01:03:44,976 --> 01:03:46,728
- I'm calling the police.
- No.

920
01:03:46,763 --> 01:03:47,973
No. Wait.

921
01:03:48,187 --> 01:03:50,607
I'll leave here first.
Then I'll call 'em.

922
01:03:50,642 --> 01:03:52,018
Be careful.

923
01:03:52,053 --> 01:03:53,395
Don't worry.

924
01:04:01,034 --> 01:04:02,279
Hey, Bob.

925
01:04:03,954 --> 01:04:06,714
I guess when I began to out you,
word somehow spread...

926
01:04:06,749 --> 01:04:12,170
and you became a liability to
your partner and he had to kill you.

927
01:04:12,588 --> 01:04:13,833
Sorry about that.

928
01:04:18,636 --> 01:04:23,349
I find it funny how I know more
about dead people than dead people.

929
01:04:23,384 --> 01:04:24,441
This is our realm, Bob.

930
01:04:24,476 --> 01:04:27,512
You can't physically harm
a living person.

931
01:04:31,984 --> 01:04:33,644
But there is that.

932
01:04:43,996 --> 01:04:46,570
Your call cannot be
completed as dialed.

933
01:04:55,258 --> 01:04:57,215
Gas.

934
01:05:25,707 --> 01:05:29,706
I'm exhausted, I'm lost,
and somewhere along the way...

935
01:05:29,741 --> 01:05:33,705
I missed an important clue
that could take me home.

936
01:05:38,637 --> 01:05:40,511
The bullet through the heart.

937
01:05:50,733 --> 01:05:53,022
It wasn't about the chief.

938
01:06:15,134 --> 01:06:17,423
God.

939
01:06:41,912 --> 01:06:45,246
Enough already, Bob. Please.

940
01:06:47,668 --> 01:06:51,500
My three least favorite words.

941
01:06:51,839 --> 01:06:53,583
Some..

942
01:06:56,010 --> 01:06:57,670
assembly...

943
01:06:57,887 --> 01:06:59,938
required.

944
01:06:59,973 --> 01:07:02,893
Simon, I've been dying to know
what that tattoo means.

945
01:07:02,928 --> 01:07:06,096
Let's just say this tattoo
is a crude obscenity.

946
01:07:08,190 --> 01:07:09,565
It's Varner.

947
01:07:10,275 --> 01:07:13,193
I once had a run-in with
some devil worshipers.

948
01:07:13,529 --> 01:07:14,988
I should've known.

949
01:07:16,657 --> 01:07:20,376
P- O-D. Prince Of Darkness.

950
01:07:20,411 --> 01:07:23,296
No wonder Varner was suspicious
when I told him...

951
01:07:23,331 --> 01:07:25,917
Fungus Bob had gotten aggressive
with me an hour earlier.

952
01:07:25,952 --> 01:07:29,167
This guy Bob Robertson
got aggressive with you?

953
01:07:29,379 --> 01:07:32,712
He had already killed Bob
5 or 6 hours before that.

954
01:07:33,008 --> 01:07:35,267
And that police van
protecting Stormy?

955
01:07:35,302 --> 01:07:37,596
That must've been Varner
waiting to follow me home...

956
01:07:37,631 --> 01:07:40,009
to bust me
for Fungus Bob's murder.

957
01:07:40,044 --> 01:07:42,387
Or shoot me while resisting arrest.

958
01:07:46,897 --> 01:07:49,156
There were no bodachs around Varner.

959
01:07:49,191 --> 01:07:51,951
But I can still feel myself
being drawn to him...

960
01:07:51,986 --> 01:07:55,521
and to the place where
he's about to commit mass murder.

961
01:08:03,665 --> 01:08:05,871
Coconut cherry chocolate chunk.

962
01:08:06,376 --> 01:08:08,452
Oh, God, no.

963
01:08:21,517 --> 01:08:23,394
Hey, Nell,
I see what the problem is.

964
01:08:23,429 --> 01:08:24,277
Stormy.

965
01:08:24,312 --> 01:08:27,231
You are eating and
reading at the same time.

966
01:08:27,266 --> 01:08:29,224
How about I eat and you read?

967
01:08:30,151 --> 01:08:33,603
No? Not so good? Okay, fine.

968
01:08:48,003 --> 01:08:51,538
All right, Varner, where are you?

969
01:09:42,936 --> 01:09:46,056
Fungus Bob didn't just
have one kill buddy.

970
01:09:47,024 --> 01:09:48,240
He had two.

971
01:09:48,275 --> 01:09:52,321
One more, and they could buy group
health insurance or form a rock band.

972
01:09:52,356 --> 01:09:54,203
Officer Eckles is checking
that right now.

973
01:09:54,204 --> 01:09:56,081
I don't know what this
Odd Thomas character knows...

974
01:09:56,116 --> 01:09:57,767
but I know that Robertson
is stupid and careless...

975
01:09:57,802 --> 01:09:59,418
and he's gonna get us nailed
if we don't do something.

976
01:09:59,453 --> 01:10:00,300
Relax.

977
01:10:00,335 --> 01:10:03,672
Did Robertson ever find those
photos at the mall he misplaced?

978
01:10:03,707 --> 01:10:08,169
I said, relax.
I'll take care of him.

979
01:10:19,647 --> 01:10:22,139
Stalking someone at the mall, Bern?

980
01:10:22,776 --> 01:10:24,436
Robertson, that idiot.

981
01:10:26,947 --> 01:10:28,824
We got to make it
look like an accident.

982
01:10:28,859 --> 01:10:30,966
Oh, it'll look like
an accident all right.

983
01:10:31,001 --> 01:10:33,073
When I find Robertson,
I'm gonna kill him.

984
01:10:33,412 --> 01:10:35,570
Already been there, done that.

985
01:10:41,420 --> 01:10:44,757
Looks like their plan was to jump
out at the end of the mall disaster

986
01:10:44,792 --> 01:10:47,379
like heroes responding to the call.

987
01:10:48,219 --> 01:10:52,051
But I never saw any bodachs
around Eckles, either.

988
01:10:52,390 --> 01:10:56,390
The presence of the bodachs
tipped me off to Fungus Bob...

989
01:10:56,425 --> 01:11:00,391
but not to his two co-conspirators,
which now seems...

990
01:11:00,732 --> 01:11:02,241
intentional.

991
01:11:02,276 --> 01:11:06,439
As if the bodachs knew of my gift,
as if they know I can see them.

992
01:11:07,823 --> 01:11:10,397
The bodachs have been
manipulating me.

993
01:11:32,015 --> 01:11:33,973
I'm gonna finish you off,
old man.

994
01:11:38,564 --> 01:11:39,780
Four.

995
01:11:39,815 --> 01:11:42,104
Well, that's just jiffy.

996
01:12:13,517 --> 01:12:16,637
This just so happens
to be my very favorite book.

997
01:12:17,271 --> 01:12:19,430
The Wonderful Wizard Of Oz.

998
01:12:19,649 --> 01:12:24,988
Officer Varner Prince of Darkness,
Officer Varner, Prince of Darkness.

999
01:12:35,082 --> 01:12:36,244
Viola.

1000
01:12:36,458 --> 01:12:38,585
- Viola! What are you doing here?
- Odd! Geez!

1001
01:12:38,620 --> 01:12:40,678
- You scared the-
- What are you doing here?

1002
01:12:40,713 --> 01:12:42,652
We had to pick out
a birthday present for Levanna.

1003
01:12:42,687 --> 01:12:45,140
And Nicolina wanted to get
a card for her big sister.

1004
01:12:45,175 --> 01:12:47,593
Look, your dream, it's happening
right here, right now.

1005
01:12:48,221 --> 01:12:50,994
I thought in a big stadium or
at the water park or a bowling alley.

1006
01:12:51,029 --> 01:12:53,768
Ladies, I need you to take Viola
and get her out of here, okay?

1007
01:12:53,803 --> 01:12:56,473
Come on.
Come on, come on. Go on.

1008
01:12:57,731 --> 01:12:59,573
This made Dorothy so very angry...

1009
01:12:59,608 --> 01:13:01,902
that she picked up the bucket
of water that stood near...

1010
01:13:01,937 --> 01:13:04,607
and dashed it all over
the wicked witch.

1011
01:13:05,530 --> 01:13:08,027
And then the wicked witch said...

1012
01:13:08,062 --> 01:13:10,525
"I'm melting! I'm melting!"

1013
01:13:13,372 --> 01:13:15,946
There's suddenly lots
of flashing lights.

1014
01:13:16,292 --> 01:13:18,865
With old-fashioned kiddie music.

1015
01:13:21,089 --> 01:13:23,046
And then I hear a big crowd.

1016
01:13:25,468 --> 01:13:28,672
And then there's the sound of water,
gushing water.

1017
01:13:32,142 --> 01:13:33,805
Bye, Nell.

1018
01:13:33,840 --> 01:13:35,469
Bye, Stormy.

1019
01:13:37,773 --> 01:13:39,650
Excuse me. Excuse me. Sorry!

1020
01:13:39,685 --> 01:13:41,192
Move, move. Excuse me!

1021
01:14:29,577 --> 01:14:32,282
A gun! He's got a gun!

1022
01:15:25,386 --> 01:15:28,921
Stormy and I are destined
to be together forever.

1023
01:15:29,766 --> 01:15:33,716
Gypsy Mummy gave us a card that
said so, for a single quarter...

1024
01:15:34,354 --> 01:15:36,845
what other couples couldn't
buy at any price.

1025
01:15:40,902 --> 01:15:42,563
No!

1026
01:16:06,471 --> 01:16:08,962
Get out of the way! Get off!

1027
01:17:11,832 --> 01:17:13,290
Hi.

1028
01:17:24,678 --> 01:17:26,007
Odd!

1029
01:17:33,646 --> 01:17:34,975
Odd!

1030
01:17:36,441 --> 01:17:38,019
It's not over.

1031
01:17:44,491 --> 01:17:45,819
It's not over.

1032
01:17:46,451 --> 01:17:49,073
It's not over. It's not over.

1033
01:17:51,999 --> 01:17:54,376
Hey Chief. What's with
the guy who shot the dogs?

1034
01:17:54,411 --> 01:17:56,665
His names Kevin Goss.

1035
01:17:57,088 --> 01:17:58,965
One of these days, bang!

1036
01:17:59,000 --> 01:18:00,127
You hear me?

1037
01:18:21,905 --> 01:18:24,823
He's got a gun!

1038
01:18:39,758 --> 01:18:41,391
- Is this your truck?
- I need a drill!

1039
01:18:41,426 --> 01:18:43,240
Do you have a drill?
I need to get this open!

1040
01:18:43,275 --> 01:18:45,020
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm a cop. Now look!

1041
01:18:45,055 --> 01:18:47,140
You see that woman?
Some maniacs just shot up the mall!

1042
01:18:47,175 --> 01:18:49,434
So either get with me,
get behind me, or get out!

1043
01:18:49,469 --> 01:18:51,012
I got a grinder!

1044
01:19:02,698 --> 01:19:05,190
Oh, my God.

1045
01:19:21,260 --> 01:19:24,179
Everyone get the hell out of here!
Get the hell out!

1046
01:19:24,214 --> 01:19:25,294
Now!

1047
01:20:12,564 --> 01:20:13,678
Hey!

1048
01:20:34,754 --> 01:20:35,999
Shit!

1049
01:20:45,724 --> 01:20:48,428
You really set yourself up, asshole!

1050
01:21:27,643 --> 01:21:30,348
It's cold in the desert.

1051
01:22:16,653 --> 01:22:19,989
I could tell my stuffing
wasn't entirely intact.

1052
01:22:20,024 --> 01:22:21,915
He's awake. He's awake!

1053
01:22:21,950 --> 01:22:24,785
But it was nothing
they couldn't stitch back together.

1054
01:22:31,668 --> 01:22:34,380
Karla told me that the chief
had come through just fine...

1055
01:22:34,415 --> 01:22:37,056
and somehow managed
to spin Fungus Bob's corpse...

1056
01:22:37,091 --> 01:22:40,709
into a bizarre cover story
that kept my secret a secret.

1057
01:22:45,725 --> 01:22:47,901
An FBI expert
on television said that

1058
01:22:47,936 --> 01:22:50,855
if you hadn't gotten
those explosives out of there,

1059
01:22:50,890 --> 01:22:53,740
at least 500 or 600 people
would've died, for sure.

1060
01:22:53,775 --> 01:22:57,725
They told me events at the Green Moon
Mall had made headlines everywhere.

1061
01:22:58,780 --> 01:23:01,272
But I didn't want to read
or see anything about it.

1062
01:23:02,951 --> 01:23:03,834
According to Eckles...

1063
01:23:03,869 --> 01:23:07,060
he and Varner started a satanic
cult when they were teenagers.

1064
01:23:07,095 --> 01:23:10,251
One night, they killed a man
and realized they enjoyed it.

1065
01:23:10,286 --> 01:23:11,551
So they kept at it,

1066
01:23:11,586 --> 01:23:14,503
eventually joining
the police force for better cover.

1067
01:23:15,548 --> 01:23:18,735
They met Robertson and Goss
and came up with a plan...

1068
01:23:18,770 --> 01:23:21,922
to infiltrate a small town
and then slowly kill it.

1069
01:23:33,400 --> 01:23:34,825
Odd! Odd! Odd!

1070
01:23:34,860 --> 01:23:37,351
Detail, present arms.

1071
01:24:03,223 --> 01:24:04,231
When I'm with you,

1072
01:24:04,266 --> 01:24:08,015
I don't have to worry about
pancakes or poltergeists.

1073
01:24:09,063 --> 01:24:12,396
When I'm with you,
I'm with my destiny.

1074
01:24:13,234 --> 01:24:16,852
Where you live, I flourish.

1075
01:24:21,868 --> 01:24:24,359
We ate food that wasn't healthy.

1076
01:24:27,082 --> 01:24:29,573
We drank too much...

1077
01:24:31,253 --> 01:24:32,913
and slept too much...

1078
01:24:39,386 --> 01:24:42,222
but could never kiss enough.

1079
01:24:42,932 --> 01:24:45,767
Everything was just as I wished.

1080
01:24:50,231 --> 01:24:54,395
- Yeah?
- Odd, it's us. Open up.

1081
01:24:55,987 --> 01:24:58,323
- Hey, guys.
- We have been calling you, Oddie.

1082
01:24:58,358 --> 01:25:00,624
I know. You know,
I disconnected the phone...

1083
01:25:00,659 --> 01:25:02,953
because the reporters won't
leave me and Stormy alone.

1084
01:25:02,988 --> 01:25:04,744
- Son.
- Do you want some-

1085
01:25:07,249 --> 01:25:09,539
You've been here long enough.

1086
01:25:09,574 --> 01:25:11,829
We think it's time to stop.

1087
01:25:12,338 --> 01:25:17,249
Sweetheart, the coroner finally
released her poor body.

1088
01:25:34,653 --> 01:25:36,444
A part of me knew...

1089
01:25:37,072 --> 01:25:40,607
from the moment I saw her
behind the ice cream counter.

1090
01:25:41,327 --> 01:25:44,162
But the truth hurt
too much to accept.

1091
01:25:45,289 --> 01:25:48,623
Her death would have been
one wound too many that day.

1092
01:25:49,794 --> 01:25:53,329
And I think I would have
let go of this life.

1093
01:26:05,227 --> 01:26:07,184
She's here, isn't she?

1094
01:26:14,403 --> 01:26:16,063
You got to let her go.

1095
01:26:17,323 --> 01:26:20,240
She deserves to move
to her next life.

1096
01:26:21,494 --> 01:26:22,822
Son...

1097
01:26:24,831 --> 01:26:26,373
it's just time.

1098
01:27:23,017 --> 01:27:24,476
I love you.

1099
01:27:27,063 --> 01:27:31,227
I promise I will see you again.
Okay?

1100
01:28:51,527 --> 01:28:54,572
Stormy always believed that life
is not about how fast you run...

1101
01:28:54,607 --> 01:28:56,730
or with what degree of grace.

1102
01:28:57,283 --> 01:28:59,333
That this life is a boot camp,

1103
01:28:59,368 --> 01:29:01,911
that we must persevere
through all the obstacles

1104
01:29:01,946 --> 01:29:04,455
and hardships to earn our way
into the next life.

1105
01:29:05,500 --> 01:29:08,750
To be with her again, I will have
the perseverance of a bulldog.

1106
01:29:10,213 --> 01:29:13,333
But sometimes, it seems to me...

1107
01:29:14,176 --> 01:29:17,296
the training
is unnecessarily painful.

1108
01:29:24,603 --> 01:29:26,654
If I live an average life-span...

1109
01:29:26,689 --> 01:29:30,023
I'll have another 60 years
before I see Stormy again.

1110
01:29:30,526 --> 01:29:32,318
That will be a long wait.

1111
01:29:34,405 --> 01:29:36,363
But I am a patient man.

1112
01:29:38,785 --> 01:29:41,074
And I have much to do.

